We have observed in part of the material (specifically from Sierra Nevada de Santa Marta ) a variation in the color pattern (“yellow trait”). The axial undulating stripes are bordered by a yellowish “shadow” [cf.
P . ( E .) fusitorsus (Oberwimmer, 1931 )
from Venezuelan Guayana (
Breure 2009
)]. Furthermore, some shells from La Guajira and Perijá regions tend to have a strong lip and a distinct parietal callus. These shells, all from low elevation localities where dry conditions prevail, are tentatively referred to this species.
